OL,6,FIn a statement issued after the
OL,7,Fpublication of the report, Sir Wyn
OL,8,Fsaid he is "critical" of the Post
OL,9,FOffice and the Government for the
OL,10,F"development and evolution" of the
OL,11,Fcompensation schemes.
OL,13,FHe also said the main scheme, the
OL,14,FHorizon Shortfall Scheme (HSS), had
OL,15,Fbeen subjected to "egregious delays".
OL,17,FIn his recommendations, Sir Wyn said
OL,18,Fclaimants who apply for compensation
OL,19,Fas part of HSS, should be entitled to
OL,20,Ffree legal advice.
